fields.description:
See https://studio.atlassian.com/browse/JST-3406

Studio overrides jira's header id and uses 'studio-header' instead of 'header'. This caused GH to stop working in IE7 due to the following greenhopper code in gh-global.js

{noformat}
document.body.insertBefore(dlg, $('header'));
{noformat}

We have worked around this issue for now in a hacky way (See JST-3406), and hopefully in the long-term the common header should ensure that the header id is uniform across all applications, but wherever possible, it will be best to avoid explicitly relying on jira's DOM because studio may replace or override jira elements in many places.

In this particular example, would it be possible to insert as the first child of the body, rather than using an insertBefore(.. 'header')?
